ody": "On Windows, the VST3 default host (e.g validator) allows to have directly a `.vst3` as a shared object but for Linux and macOS, we need to generate a full plugin structure (documentation [here](https://steinbergmedia.github.io/vst3_dev_portal/pages/Technical+Documentation/Locations+Format/Plugin+Locations.html)).\r\n\r\nOn macOS, we also need to generate a `Info.plist` as we do currently for NPlug.Validator [here](https://github.com/xoofx/NPlug/blob/main/src/NPlug.Validator/build/Info.plist)\r\n\r\nProbably the best option would be to create a new MSBuild target `PublishVst` to generate a compatible VST3 folder structure.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/xoofx/NPlug/issues/1/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/xoofx/NPlug/issues/1/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}]}